articles.title: Thailand warns clashes with Cambodia could move towards war as 138,000 flee fighting
articles.content: SURIN, Thailand: Thailand's acting Prime Minister Phumtham Wechayachai warned Friday (Jul 25) that cross-border clashes with Cambodia that have uprooted more than 130,000 people "could develop into war", as the countries traded deadly strikes for a second day

articles.title: Iran meets European powers amid threats of UN sanctions snapback
articles.content: Iranian diplomats met counterparts from Germany, Britain and France on Friday for renewed nuclear talks, amid warnings that the three European powers could trigger "snapback" sanctions outlined under the 2015 deal. There was no immediate information given by either side about the meeting

articles.title: Motorcyclist, 23, dies in accident involving lorry near Woodlands Checkpoint
articles.content: A 23-year-old motorcyclist died after an accident with a lorry near Woodlands Checkpoint on Friday (July 25) morning. A lorry is seen stationary on the road shoulder.
